      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. Methyl isocyanate</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Chemical hazards&nbsp;</strong>in <strong>industries</strong> due to <strong>accidental leakage</strong> of <strong>chemical substances</strong>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Bhopal gas tragedy is a Single exposure Point source type of Epidemic occured on 3 december 1984 from union carbide plant.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:&nbsp;</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>gas</strong> responsible for <strong>Bhopal gas tragedy</strong> was:&nbsp;<strong>Methyl isocyanate</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Textbook of Community Medicine by Rajvir Balwar, pg 734; Park 27/e p928-929</strong></span></p>",
