      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">A junior resident is assessing the economic well-being of a rural area as part of her postgraduate project. She recalls the criteria used to define the poverty line for rural areas in terms of purchasing capacity. According to this criterion, what is the threshold for calorie intake per person per day below which an individual in a rural area is considered below the poverty line?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4528120",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34640,
      "difficulty_level": "difficult",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. C. 2400</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Poverty threshold (poverty line):&nbsp;</strong>Is the <strong>minimum level</strong> of <strong>income</strong> deemed necessary to <strong>achieve</strong> an <strong>adequate standard</strong> of <strong>living.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Rural area -</strong>&nbsp;The <strong>poverty line</strong> is the <strong>inability</strong> to <strong>buy adequate food calories</strong> equivalent to <strong>2400 per day/head.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Urban area</strong> -<strong> Inability</strong> to <strong>buy adequate food calories</strong> equivalent to <strong>2100 per day/head.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Below Poverty Line</strong> (BPL) population in India -&nbsp;</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>22% </strong>(Tendulkar Committee 2011-12)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>29.5%</strong> (Rangarajan Committee 2014)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>11.3%</strong> (Niti Aayog 2022-23)</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Below Poverty Line (BPL) Criteria -&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/08/12/screenshot-2024-08-12-161445.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"551\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Textbook of community medicine, Rajvir Balwar, Pg 84.</strong></span></p>",
